    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Create CGU group and cash generating units (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>In Japan, an impairment on fixed assets can be based on either individual fixed assets or cash generating units.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create CGU group and cash generating units (Japan)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In Japan, an impairment on fixed assets can be based on either individual fixed assets or cash generating units.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When measuring impairment based on cash generating units, the first step is to group the fixed assets into cash generating units.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Multiple sets of cash generating units are allowed so that you can choose the most appropriate CGU.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This is achieved through the creation of CGU groups.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure walks you through creating CGU groups and cash generating units.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You will also learn how to assign fixed assets to cash generating units and how to assign shared assets and goodwill to CGU groups.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In order to complete this task, the Fixed Asset configuration key must be selected.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure was created using the demo data company JPMF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create a CGU group</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Setup &gt; Impairment &gt; CGU groups.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can create multiple CGU groups for testing if you are not sure about the appropriate combinations of fixed assets and cash generating units.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the CGU group field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Description field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Impairment of goodwill and shared asset field, select an option.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select the method according to your corporate policy.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create cash generating units under the CGU group</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Note the value in the Cash generating unit number field to reference later</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You will need to reference this value when you configure the cash generating unit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Note the value in the Cash generating unit number field to reference later</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You will need to reference this value when you configure the cash generating unit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Assign shared assets and goodwill to the CGU group</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Expand the Shared assets and goodwill section.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Massive import.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>We recommend that you specify a condition that adds all the assets with that hit with the condition at once.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="134" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can also enter asset one by one in the grid.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="135" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Criteria field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="136" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="137" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Configure cash generating units</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="138" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Assign fixed assets.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="139" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the Quick Filter to find the CGU to edit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="140" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enter the first cash generating unit number that you noted previously.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="141" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Massive import.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="142" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>We recommend you to specify a condition that adds all the assets with that hit with the condition at once.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="143" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can also enter asset one by one in the grid.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="144" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Criteria field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="145" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example: Location = FUKUOKA</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="146" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="147" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Undiscounted cash flow field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="148" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Recoverable value field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="149" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="150" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the Quick Filter to find the cash generating unit to edit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="151" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enter the second cash generating unit number that you noted previously.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="152" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Massive import.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="153" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Criteria field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="154" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example: Location = OSAKA</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="155" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="156" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Undiscounted cash flow field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="157" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Recoverable value field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="158" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="159" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Activate the CGU group</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="160" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Activate.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="161" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Only active CGU groups are allowed to run recognition tests.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="162" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Yes.</source>
        </trans-unit>
      </group>
    </body>
